                             <locus from="1ra" to="77vb"/>
                              <seg type="script">Late 15th/first half of the 16th century.</seg>
                              <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                              <desc>Careful, very irregular; by a mediocre scribe.
                                Right-sloping, broadly spaced letters. The slant and size of the letters deviate significantly;
                                the written lines are
                                biased on many folia. The word and sentence dividers are set up very close to
                              the bottom line (under the vowel marker if the preceding characther has any);
                              especially the word dividers are compressed,
